# Corrected Response

Modern email evolved through contributions from multiple researchers and computer networking projects. One of the most widely recognized milestones was Ray Tomlinson's implementation of networked email in 1971 on ARPANET, including the use of the "@" symbol to separate the user name from the host computer.

Rather than having a single inventor, email developed over time through contributions from many individuals and organizations.

---

# Reflection

## What I Learned

Hallucinations are not limited to small factual mistakes. AI models may confidently invent people, dates, awards, organizations, or historical events that never existed.

---

## What I'd Do Differently

When evaluating historical claims, I would verify names, dates, organizations, and awards independently instead of assuming that detailed responses are accurate.

